article.headline: Albany 71, New Hampshire 64
article.story: Durham, N.H. (AP) -- Jamar Wilson scored 23 points to help Albany beat New Hampshire 71-64 on Sunday. The Great Danes (14-8, 7-2 America East) have won four straight and six of their last seven. New Hampshire (8-14, 4-5) trailed 48-35 with 12:07 remaining. The Wildcats rallied behind Tyrece Gibbs, who scored 17 of his 21 points in the second half. Gibbs made three consecutive 3-pointers that closed the gap to 64-62 with 2:22 left. Albany still led 66-64 in the final minute, when Wilson hit a spinning turnaround on a drive into the lane. After Brent Wilson took a charge on Jermaine Anderson's move to the basket, the Great Danes sealed the win at the foul line.
